Label: SC_CARRIER_SPECIFIC
Comment: "http://www.appel118.fr/detail.php lists 118777 as only being accessible from SFR. 224\nis an Orange-only service."

Label: SC_PREMIUM_RATE
Comment:
"SMS Services [4-8]\d{4} vary in price from 0.05 euro to 4.50 euro per SMS, based on
prefix - we consider these all premium rate for now. All 118 XYZ numbers are considered
here as it is given ""libre"" which does not mean zero cost instead it is up to the
provider http://www.telecom-infoconso.fr/les-numeros-08-et-les-numeros-courts/"

Label: SC_SHORT_CODE
Comment: "110 is a number used for different campaigns such as Sidaction for a limited time only."

Label: SC_STANDARD_RATE
Comment: "3646 is listed as being the same as a local call on www.ameli.fr."

Label: SC_TOLL_FREE
Comment: "Includes some ""urgent services"" numbers, plus short-codes designated as being free of\ncost and European harmonised numbers (116XXX)."

Label: SC_TOLL_FREE
Comment: "740 is listed as carrier-specific and toll-free on contact.orange.fr."

Label: XML
Comment: "Short numbers will be formatted as a block without a national prefix."

Label: XML_MOBILE
Comment:
"700 numbers are mobile phone services as per https://www.arcep.fr/index.php?id=8146
where length is mentioned as 'extended length numbers'. As we are not sure, supporting
it as regular 9 digit range. Sub ranges are assigned to mobile operators as per:
https://www.arcep.fr/index.php?id=interactivenumeros&no_cache=1"

Label: XML_UAN
Comment: "80[6-9] numbers cost the same as fixed-line calls, but are not geographically assigned,\nso we classify them as UAN."

Label: XML_VOIP
Comment: "087 numbers used to be used for this."
